        <briefdescription>
<para>Convenience function that disconnects all available ifaces that support connectivity without putting them into admin-down state (unless auto-down is enabled for the iface). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Essentially a wrapper for <ref refid="group__net__if_1ga2187650062d6139b9f4b81745a206803" kindref="member">net_if_down</ref>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>skip_ignored</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>- If true, only affect ifaces that aren&apos;t ignored by conn_mgr. Otherwise, affect all ifaces. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 if all net_if_up and conn_mgr_if_connect calls returned 0, otherwise the first nonzero value returned by either net_if_up or conn_mgr_if_connect. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
